-------------------------------------------------Store Prcoedure--------------------------------------------
A Stored Procedure in SQL is a precompiled collection of one or more SQL statements stored in the database.
It can accept input parameters, perform operations, and return results.
Stored procedures help reuse code, improve performance, and maintain security.

CREATE PROCEDURE procedure_name
    @parameter1 datatype,
    @parameter2 datatype OUTPUT -- optional
AS
BEGIN
    -- SQL statements
END;

Execution:

EXEC GetEmployeesByDepartment 'IT';




